Third-party reuse notice
========================

This package is MIT-licensed and includes implementation ideas and API design
adaptations from the FastqIndEx project:

  https://github.com/DKFZ-ODCF/FastqIndEx

FastqIndEx is distributed under the MIT License.

Upstream reference (paths and lineage; vendored files may differ where adapted):
- Repository: https://github.com/DKFZ-ODCF/FastqIndEx
- Branch: `master`
- Commit: `e21ef731a1f3341e5ac4525146891689e0cbf9ce` (2021-06-21)

Reuse/compliance notes:
- Retain MIT licensing for reused/adapted portions.
- Preserve attribution to the original FastqIndEx project.
- Keep this notice updated when additional upstream source files are vendored
  or modified.

Current adaptation scope:
- Vendored/adapted core algorithms in:
  - src/fastqindex_core/common/CommonStructsAndConstants.h
  - src/fastqindex_core/process/base/IndexEntry.h
  - src/fastqindex_core/process/base/ZLibBasedFASTQProcessorBaseClass.h
  - src/fastqindex_core/process/base/ZLibBasedFASTQProcessorBaseClass.cpp
  - src/fastqindex_core/process/index/Indexer.h
  - src/fastqindex_core/process/index/Indexer.cpp
  - src/fastqindex_core/process/extract/Extractor.h
  - src/fastqindex_core/process/extract/Extractor.cpp
- Local gzip FASTA/FASTQ indexing and extraction behavior shaped after the
  FastqIndEx indexing/extraction model.
- R/Rcpp-facing API designed for in-memory index handling.

Annotated local changes in adapted core:
- fastqindexr change: Replace FastqIndEx Source/Sink abstractions with
  std::ifstream and in-memory index registry token handling.
- fastqindexr change: Keep dictionary payload uncompressed in memory (no .fqi
  serialization path in this package).
- fastqindexr change: Dense-region extraction planner for arbitrary index
  vectors with result reordering to caller order.
- fastqindexr change: Current FASTA extraction path assumes one sequence line
  per record (record_size=2).
